The paper deals with the optimization of a receiver for ultra wideband (UWB) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of genetic algorithms (GA) also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of minimum mean square error (MMSE) techniques, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
